pd_1_com_0text: I'm here now. That's all that matters.
pd_4_com_0text: You've got bags under your eyes. Sleepless night?
pd_4_com_1text: You look like you got run over by a train.
pd_5_com_0text: Just had a lot on my mind.
pd_6_com_0text: Just what I needed to hear this evening.
pd_7_com_0text: Were you worried about the game?
pd_8_com_0text: I have nothing to be worried about.
pd_9_com_0text: You are so confident. Is it because of the "gift for cards" that you so eagerly believe in?
pd_10_com_0text: I don't just believe. I have it.
pd_15_com_1text: That's amusing. Luck always runs out.
pd_16_com_0text: I am done with this conversation.
pd_19_com_0text: Last game, you seemed like you knew a lot about me. What's the deal with that?
pd_20_com_0text: I've had plenty of time to get to know you.
pd_21_com_0text: Yet another thing I don't remember.
pd_22_com_0text: You miss your memories so much, yet you don't try your hardest to win.
pd_23_com_0text: Hard to miss my freedom when I don't remember what it feels like.
pd_23_com_1text: I won last time, haven't I?
pd_24_com_0text: So quick to give up. I thought better of you.
pd_25_com_0text: One win among thousands of losses. What a thing to be proud of.
pd_26_com_0text: At least I can hold my temper when I lose.
pd_26_com_1text: You are annoying, you know that, right?
pd_27_com_0text: How would you know? You don’t remember our games.
pd_29_com_0text: A lot has changed since then.
pd_30_com_0text: I will take that as a compliment.
pd_32_com_0text: Don’t tell me what to do with my compliments.
pd_36_com_0text: What did I tell you? I have a gift for cards.
pd_37_com_0text: Such a rare event. I am so lucky to be here to witness it.
pd_38_com_0text: Don't be so petty. Losing is hard, but you should be used to it by now.
pd_39_com_0text: At least I’m not throwing a tantrum like you did.
pd_40_com_0text: Say whatever you wish. You lost, fair and square.
pd_41_com_0text: I did, but don’t forget we have one more game to play.
pd_41_com_1text: The only square thing about this is your face.
pd_42_com_0text: Yes, because I’m in a portrait.
pd_44_com_0text: Come on, that was a good joke.
pd_47_com_0text: Anyway, I must take my leave, but we have one more game to play.
pd_48_com_0text: One game that will decide all.
